# Backend Rules (NestJS)

## Architecture

- **Pattern**: Controllers → Services → Repositories (TypeORM)
- **Module structure**: Each feature has its own module in `src/modules/`
- Shared utilities go in `src/common/`
- Database entities go in `src/database/entities/`

## File Naming

- `*.controller.ts` — HTTP route handlers
- `*.service.ts` — Business logic
- `*.entity.ts` — TypeORM entities
- `*.dto.ts` — Data Transfer Objects
- `*.module.ts` — NestJS modules
- `*.guard.ts` — Auth/permission guards
- `*.spec.ts` — Test files (colocated)

## Conventions

- Use `class-validator` decorators for DTO validation
- Use `class-transformer` for serialization (`@Exclude`, `@Expose`)
- Entities must extend or follow TypeORM patterns with `@Entity`, `@Column`, etc.
- Use NestJS dependency injection — never instantiate services manually
- Use `@ApiTags`, `@ApiOperation` for Swagger documentation
- Handle errors with NestJS built-in exceptions (`NotFoundException`, `BadRequestException`, etc.)
- Use TypeORM QueryBuilder for complex queries, repository methods for simple CRUD

## Commands

```bash
cd backend
npm run start:dev    # Dev server (port 4001)
npm run build        # Build
npm test             # Run all tests
npx jest --testPathPattern="<pattern>"  # Run specific tests
```

## Path Aliases

- `@/*` maps to `src/*` (see tsconfig.json)
